  "body": "## The problem\r\n\r\nTowards the end of the [Unicode Properties section of Regexes](https://docs.perl6.org/language/regexes#Unicode_Properties) there is a table of five character class combining operators but AFAIK only `+` and `-` work and the other three - `&`, `|`, `^` do not seem to combine classes.  You might use `&` conjunction to get a similar effect like the `posix_alnum` example below but that is not how the operators are presented in the documentation.\r\n\r\nIRC discussion here: https://irclog.perlgeek.de/perl6/2018-05-26#i_16210067\r\n\r\n```Perl6\r\nmy token posix_alnum { <+alnum - [_]> & <:ascii> };\r\nmy $latin-chars = [~] chr(0)..chr(0xFF); \r\nsay $latin-chars.comb(/<posix_alnum>/).join\r\n\r\nOUTPUT: \r\n0123456789ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZabcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz‚ê§\r\n```\r\n## Suggestions\r\n\r\nIf the operators don't work in this context they should be removed and the section may need a little rewriting.  The use of conjunction to get the effect of intersection might be mentioned.\r\n",
